In [11]:
under_25_data = [72, 70.8, 67.2, 65.4, 67]
over_25_data = [100 - percent for percent in under_25_data]
figure, axes = plt.subplots()
axes.bar(range(len(under_25_data)), under_25_data, label="Under 25", alpha=0.5, color='b')
axes.bar(range(len(over_25_data)), over_25_data, bottom=under_25_data, label="Over 25", alpha=0.5, color='r')
plt.sca(axes)
plt.xticks([0, 1, 2, 3, 4], ['1972', '1973', '1974', '1975', '1976'])
axes.set_ylabel("Percentage")
axes.set_xlabel("Year")
plt.legend(loc='best')
plt.show()

cocaine_data_actual = [0.3, 0.2, 0.0]
cocaine_data_perceived = [48.4, 5.3, 1.2]
ind = np.arange(3)

x_labels = ['1-9 Times', '10-29 Times', 'Daily']
width = 0.25

figure, axes = plt.subplots()

rect1 = axes.bar(ind, cocaine_data_actual, width, color="steelblue", align="center")
rect2 = axes.bar(ind + width, cocaine_data_perceived, width, color="lightcoral", align="center")
axes.set_xticks([0, 1,2])
axes.set_xticklabels(x_labels, rotation=40)
axes.yaxis.grid( b=True, which="major")
axes.set_ylim((0, 100))
axes.set_ylabel("Percentage")
plt.title("Cocaine Usage")
axes.legend((rect1[0], rect2[0]), ('Actual', 'Perceived'))
plt.show()
